				";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:7:"english";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:2:{s:4:"name";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Derek Jones";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:7:"english";}}s:5:"email";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:24:"derek.jones@ellislab.com";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:7:"english";}}}}}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"term";s:17:"CP Accessory Feed";s:6:"scheme";s:60:"https://expressionengine.com/blog/category/cp-accessory-feed";s:5:"label";s:17:"CP Accessory Feed";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:7:"english";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"term";s:16:"ExpressionEngine";s:6:"scheme";s:59:"https://expressionengine.com/blog/category/expressionengine";s:5:"label";s:16:"ExpressionEngine";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:7:"english";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"term";s:4:"News";s:6:"scheme";s:47:"https://expressionengine.com/blog/category/news";s:5:"label";s:4:"News";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:7:"english";}}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1121:"
				<p>ExpressionEngine 3 has entered the first phase of its <abbr title="End of Life">EOL</abbr>, that of becoming a <em>legacy product</em>. A legacy product is no longer developed actively, but still receives critical security patches and is eligible for support for one year. This means that <strong>ExpressionEngine 3 will be retired on December 14, 2018</strong>. You can read more about our <abbr title="End of Life">EOL</abbr> policy for legacy software <a href="https://expressionengine.com/support/faq#what-is-a-legacy-product-what-is-a-retired-product">in the Support FAQ</a>.</p>

<p>If you upgrade a version 3 license to ExpressionEngine 4, you will still have access to the v3 download, in case critical patches are released before you make the jump to v4.</p>

<p>Thus, we have just released ExpressionEngine 3.5.13, the final &#8220;normal&#8221; patch release for version 3. It includes a small handful of bug fixes and adds PHP 7.2 compatibility. You can find details in the <a href="https://docs.expressionengine.com/v3/about/changelog.html#version-3-5-13">ExpressionEngine 3 change log</a>.</p>

